132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 876
H.P. 562 House of Representatives, March 4, 2025
An Act to Support Rural Resilience and Emergency Response
Through the Maine Service Fellows Program
Reference to the Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative RIELLY of Westbrook.
Cosponsored by Senator BENNETT of Oxford and
Representatives: DANA of the Passamaquoddy Tribe, EATON of Deer Isle, MALON of
Biddeford, PLUECKER of Warren.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §7503, sub-§13-A, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 155, §2, is amended
3 to read:
4 13-A. Maine Service Fellows Program. Develop and administer the Maine Service
5 Fellows Program under section 7506; and
6 Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §7503, sub-§14, as enacted by PL 1995, c. 54, §1, is amended to
7 read:
8 14. Annual report. Submit an annual report to the Governor, the Legislature and the
9 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over state and local
10 government matters by January 31st of each year.; and
11 Sec. 3. 5 MRSA §7503, sub-§15 is enacted to read:
12 15. Disaster response. In conjunction with the Department of Defense, Veterans and
13 Emergency Management, compile a list of volunteers who are available at the request of
14 the Governor during states of emergency to provide emergency response and support
15 services in coordination with the Maine Emergency Management Agency. The list of
16 volunteers must include individuals who completed a term of service through an approved
17 national service position under the Corporation for National and Community Service
18 authorized under 42 United States Code, Section 12651 and veterans.
19 Sec. 4. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
20 allocations are made.
21 MAINE OFFICE OF COMMUNITY AFFAIRS
22 Maine Service Fellows Program Z417
23 Initiative: Provides ongoing funds for 20 program fellows to participate in the Maine
24 Service Fellows Program.
25 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
26 All Other $700,000 $700,000
27 __________ __________
28 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $700,000 $700,000
29
25 SUMMARY
3206 This bill provides ongoing funds for 20 program fellows to participate in the Maine
3217 Service Fellows Program. The bill also directs the Maine Commission for Community
3228 Service, in conjunction with the Department of Defense, Veterans and Emergency
3239 Management, to compile a list of volunteers who are available at the request of the
3340 Governor during states of emergency to provide emergency response and support services
3351 in coordination with the Maine Emergency Management Agency.
